  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Inspect front ball joints"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Since the vehicle body vibrates strongly during ball joint inspection, the jack-up point must be supported by a jack stand or other means to hold the vehicle body securely."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lift Set",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "G000319",
          "label": "Lift Set",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Front wheel removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Front wheel removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Ball joint Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "664_3.0_jpn_11035713_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "664_3.0_jpn_11035714_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Inspect the mounting bolts, nuts, and bushings of suspension components to ensure that they are not loose, damaged, or deteriorated. Shake the lower arm end (A) up and down in small increments to inspect the ball joint for rattling (B). B in the illustration shows where rattling occurs in the ball joint.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000665",
          "label": "The lower arm shall be replaced.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If there is rattling in the ball joint, The lower arm shall be replaced."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Ball Joint Boot Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "664_3.0_jpn_11412996_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the ball joint boot is cracked, leaking grease or has evidence of grease leakage, The lower arm shall be replaced.",
        "Ball joint If the boot has cracks due to deterioration or other causes, but there is no grease leakage or no evidence of grease leakage, Ball joint boots shall be replaced."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Front wheel mounting",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Front wheel mounting",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
